name: logical-unification
documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the "logical-unification" package version 0.4.6, released on May 6, 2023, available on PyPI (Python Package Index). It provides a Python library for logical unification, extendable via dispatch, and supports Python versions 3.6 and above. The package, licensed under the BSD License, is designed for developers and researchers in science. It includes features for unifying Python data types, custom classes, and function dispatch through pattern matching. The project emphasizes performance and reliability, showcasing benchmarks for its stream-based approach to handling deeply nested structures. Installation instructions, examples of usage, and development details are provided, along with links to the project's homepage and GitHub statistics.
